name: City of Renton v. Playtime Theatres, Inc.
question: Did the Renton ordinance violate either the First or Fourteenth Amendment?

name: Equal Employment Opportunity Commission v. Federal Labor Relations Authority
Louisiana Public Service Commission v. Federal Communications Commission
Bethel School District No. 403 v. Fraser
question: Does the First Amendment prevent a school district from disciplining a high school student for giving a lewd speech at a high school assembly?
description: A case in which the Court held that public schools have the right to prohibit the use of vulgar and offensive language.

name: Dow Chemical Company v. United States
question: Does the Fourth Amendment require government inspectors to obtain warrants before conducting aerial searches of outdoor business facilities?

name: Brown-Forman Distillers Corporation v. New York State Liquor Authority
Pacific Gas & Electric Company v. Public Utilities Commission of California
International Longshoremen's Association, AFL-CIO v. Davis
Bender v. Williamsport Area School District
Regents of the University of Michigan v. Ewing
question: Did the University arbitrarily interfere with Ewing’s property, and therefore violate his right to Due Process under the Fourteenth Amendment, by revoking his admission to the medical program?

name: Meritor Savings Bank, FSB v. Vinson
question: Did the Civil Rights Act prohibit the creation of a "hostile environment" or was it limited to tangible economic discrimination in the workplace?

name: Batson v. Kentucky
question: Did the prosecutor's use of peremptory challenges to exclude the four blacks from the jury violate Batson's Sixth and Fourteenth Amendment rights to a fair jury trial and his Fourteenth Amendment right to equal protection of the laws?

name: Cuyahoga Valley Railway Company v. United Transportation Union
Thornburgh v. American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists
question: Did the Pennsylvania requirements unconstitutionally interfere with the right to privacy?

name: Attorney General of New York v. Soto-Lopez
Nantahala Power & Light Company v. Thornburg
California v. Ciraolo
question: Did the warrantless, aerial observation of Ciraolo's back yard from an altitude of 1,000 feet constitute an illegal search and violate the Fourth Amendment?

name: Transcontinental Gas Pipe Line Corporation v. State Oil and Gas Board of Mississippi
Lockhart v. McCree
question: During a capital trial does the Constitution prohibit the removal of prospective jurors whose opposition to the death penalty is so strong that it would prevent or substantially impair the performance of their duties at the sentencing phase of the trial?

name: Public Serv. Comm'n of Md. v. Chesapeake & Potomac Telephone Co. of Md.
United States Dept. of the Treasury, Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms v. Galioto
Three Affiliated Tribes of Fort Berthold Reservation v. Wold Engineering, P. C.
Local 28 of the Sheet Metal Workers' International Association v. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission
question: Did provisions of Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964 empower courts to order race-conscious membership quotas?

name: Pennsylvania v. Delaware Valley Citizens' Council for Clean Air
question:
(1) Did the Clean Air Act authorize attorneys' fees for DVCCCA and EPA’s non-litigation activities?

(2) Did the Third Circuit properly affirm awarded multipliers for DVCCCA and EPA’s superior work opposing Pennsylvania’s motion to stay the consent decree?

name: Press-Enterprise Co. v. Superior Court of Cal., County of Riverside
question:
(1) Does the public’s constitutional right to access criminal proceedings extend to pre trial proceedings?

(2) Does the standard for closed preliminary hearings under the California Penal Code violate the constitutional rights of the public?

name: Murray v. Carrier
question: Should a claim that would otherwise be prohibited by state court procedural rules barring claims not raised in an initial appeal be permitted if a defendant can prove that the omission was due entirely to an attorney's mistake (rather than to a tactical decision)?

name: Merrell Dow Pharmaceuticals Inc. v. Thompson
Michigan v. Jackson
question: When a defendant requests counsel at an arraignment, are the police allowed to initiate interrogations before that defendant has had a chance to consult with the appointed counsel?
description: A case in which the Court held that when a defendant requests counsel at an arraignment, the are not police allowed to initiate interrogations before that defendant has had a chance to consult with the appointed counsel.

name: Aetna Life Insurance Company v. Lavoie
Goldman v. Weinberger
question: Did the Air Force Regulation violate the Free Exercise Clause of the First Amendment?

name: Golden State Transit Corporation v. City of Los Angeles
City of Los Angeles v. Preferred Communications, Inc.
United States v. American College of Physicians
question: Were advertisements for medical products in the American College of Physicians' medical journal "substantially related" to the organization's tax-exempt purpose of maintaining high standards in medicine, and therefore tax-exempt?

name: United States v. City of Fulton
question: Can the Secretary of Energy or his delegates impose new hydro-electricity prices on an interim basis under Section 5 of the Flood Control Act of 1944?

name: Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System v. Dimension Financial Corporation
Vasquez v. Hillery
question:
(1) Did Hillery exhaust all avenues for habeas corpus relief in state court even though the federal district court requested additional evidence?

(2) Did Hillery's eventual conviction render any discrimination in the indictment process "harmless error"?

name: Wisconsin Department of Industry, Labor and Human Relations v. Gould, Inc.
Heath v. Alabama
question: Does the Double Jeopardy Clause of the Fifth Amendment prevent two separate states from trying an individual for the same crime?
description: A case in which the Court held that the doctrine of dual sovereignty grants each state the right to try a criminal under the laws of that state, regardless of whether he had already been tried under the laws of another state.

name: Pennsylvania Bureau of Correction v. United States Marshals Service
Bowers v. Hardwick
question: Does the Constitution confer a fundamental right upon homosexuals to engage in consensual sodomy, thereby invalidating the laws of many states which make such conduct illegal?
description: A case in which the Court held that there was no constitutional protection for sodomy, and that states could outlaw its practice.

name: South Carolina v. Catawba Indian Tribe, Inc.
Chicago Teachers Union, Local No. 1, AFT, AFL-CIO v. Hudson
McLaughlin v. United States
question: Is an unloaded handgun a "dangerous weapon" within the meaning of the federal bank robbery statute?

name: AT&T Technologies, Inc. v. Communications Workers of America
Wardair Canada v. Florida Dept. Of Revenue
Memphis Community School District v. Stachura
Dennison Manufacturing Company v. Panduit Corporation
Federal Trade Commission v. Indiana Federation of Dentists
United States v. Riverside Bayview Homes, Inc.
Commodity Futures Trading Commission v. Schor
California State Board of Equalization v. Chemehuevi Indian Tribe
Parsons Steel, Inc. v. First Alabama Bank
Connolly v. Pension Benefit Guaranty Corp.
United States v. Hughes Properties, Inc.
question: Can Hughes deduct the fixed jackpot amount as a business expense at the end of each fiscal year?

name: Turner v. Murray
question: In a capital case involving an interracial crime, is the defendant entitled to have potential jurors informed of the victim's race and questioned about any potential racial biases?

name: MacDonald, Sommer & Frates v. County of Yolo
City of Riverside v. Rivera
question: Is an award of attorney's fees under the Civil Rights Attorney's Fees Awards Act of 1976 "unreasonable" within the meaning of the statute if it exceeds the amount of damages recovered by the plaintiff in the underlying civil rights action?

name: East River Steamship Corporation v. Transamerica Delaval Inc.
question: When a product fails as a result of design and manufacturing flaws, damaging only itself and causing only economic harm, can the owner of the product bring suit against the manufacturer under the negligence or products-liability doctrines of tort law?

name: Lake Coal Co. v. Roberts & Schaeffer Co.
Anderson v. Liberty Lobby, Inc.
question: Can a court, in the context of a summary judgment request, award summary judgment in a libel action if the moving party had no evidence that a reasonable jury might disbelieve its opponent's claim?

name: Wygant v. Jackson Board of Education
question: Did the collective bargaining agreement provision for race-based layoffs violate the Fourteenth Amendment's Equal Protection Clause?

name: Maine v. Taylor
question: Did the Maine law unconstitutionally burden interstate commerce, violating the Commerce Clause?

name: Bowen v. Michigan Academy of Family Physicians
Square D Company v. Niagara Frontier Tariff Bureau, Inc.
question: If prices were fixed in such a way that should be forbidden by the Sherman Act and should not have been approved by the Interstate Commerce Commission, should the carriers be subject to treble damages?

name: United States v. American Bar Endowment
Bowen v. Public Agencies Opposed to Social Security Entrapment
Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation v. Philadelphia Gear Corporation
question: Is a standby letter of credit backed by a contingent promissory note insured as a "deposit" under the federal deposit insurance program?

name: Witters v. Washington Department of Services for the Blind
question: Did the First Amendment’s Establishment Clause prohibit Washington from funding Witters’ ministerial education through the state’s vocational rehabilitation program?

name: Moran v. Burbine
question: Does the self-incrimination clause of the Fifth Amendment require the suppression of three confessions and three valid waivers of rights, when an attorney unrequested by the defendant was given misleading information by a police officer about interrogations and the defendant was not informed of the attorney's call?
description: A case in which the Court held that failure to inform Burbine about the attorney’s phone call did not affect the validity of his waiver of rights.

name: Bowen v. Roy
question: Does the free exercise clause of the First Amendment provide an exception to the social security number requirement to receive state and federal welfare benefits?
description: A case in which the Court that the free exercise clause of the First Amendment does not provide an exception to the social security number requirement to receive state and federal welfare benefits.

name: Japan Whaling Association v. American Cetacean Society
Posadas de Puerto Rico Associates, dba Condado Holiday Inn v. Tourism Company of Puerto Rico
question: Did the law violate the First Amendment?

name: Ford v. Wainwright
question:
1. Does the cruel and unusual punishment clause of the Eighth Amendment and the due process clause of the Fourteenth Amendment prohibit the imposition of the death penalty upon the insane?

  2. Did the Federal District Court err when it declined to hear Ford's petition?

name: Malley v. Briggs
question: Is a police officer entitled to immunity when he causes an unlawful arrest by presenting a judge with an application for a warrant that does not present a probable cause?
description: A case in which the Court held that a police officer was not entitled to immunity when he caused an unlawful arrest by presenting a judge with an application for a warrant that did not present a probable cause.

name: United States Department of Transportation v. Paralyzed Veterans of America
International Union, United Automobile, Aerospace, and Agricultural Implement Workers of America v. Brock
Midlantic National Bank v. New Jersey Department of Environmental Protection
Davis v. Bandemer
question: Did Indiana's 1981 state apportionment violate the Equal Protection Clause of the Fourteenth Amendment?

name: Thornburg v. Gingles
question: Did the District Court err by holding that a North Carolina redistricting plan unlawfully discriminated against blacks in six voting districts?

name: City of Los Angeles v. Heller
New York v. P. J. Video, Inc.
question: If a warrant is issued for the seizure of items that can be considered as mediums of speech, does the First Amendment require this warrant to satisfy a "higher" level of proof for probable-cause than warrants issued for other forms of evidence?

name: Philadelphia Newspapers Inc. v. Hepps
question: Did the state supreme court's decision violate the First Amendment?

name: Ohio Civil Rights Commission v. Dayton Christian Public Schools, Inc.
question: Should the district court have abstained from adjudicating the case?
description: A case in which the Court held that federal courts should abstain from adjudicating civil state proceedings in which important state interests are involved.

name: Firefighters v. City of Cleveland
question: Does Section 706(g) of Title VII preclude a court from approving a consent decree that provides relief that may benefit individuals who were not the actual victims of the defendant’s discriminatory practices?
description: A case in which the Court held that section 706(g) of Title VII does not apply to relief awarded in a consent decree.

name: Sorenson v. Secretary of the Treasury
Matsushita Electric Industrial Company, Ltd. v. Zenith Radio Corporation
question: Did the Court of Appeals apply the proper standards in evaluating the decision of the district court?
description: A case in which the Court held that evidence of alleged conspiracies is not sufficient to prove allegations of violating antitrust legislation unless there is evidence that the conspiracies in question injured American companies.

name: Bowen v. City of New York
National Labor Relations Board v. Financial Institution Employees of America, Local 1182, Chartered by United Food & Commercial Workers International Union, AFL-CIO
Bowsher v. Synar
question: Did the functions assigned by Congress to the Comptroller General of the United States under the Gramm-Rudman-Hollings Deficit Control Act of 1985 violate the doctrine of separation of powers?
